item.title: I need help!and fast got damn!
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

Download a source for some servers you need different Java types so watch out. If one java edition does not work try another till you get the right one or look for codes you can place in the compile button it may work even with the wrong java edition but you will not be able to keep the edits you make and after each edit always compile your server and sometimes it will tell you if there is and error so you can change it. The main thing to edit is Client.java. If you wish to edit a characters stats simply open up Characters file choose the file you wish and if its you and your want 135 all stats just make your self a admin by typing 3 in player rights then logging in and typing ::master if oyu need any help fell free to add me on msn : junaidasif@hotmail.co.uk

Plus dont have that many server Ips as when they all try to run your server your pc will probally mess up and your server just lagg badly .

item.dc:creator: @asd2 asd
item.description:
@asd2 wrote:

where i do that in my CPU???

Copied from ultimate server guide:

Now we will need to make the rule for your router, by doing this you need to go into your router. You can do this by going into Internet Explorer (or whatever client you use for the Internet), and then type in the IP address of the router. Now log into the router and go into “advanced” (at top of screen on mine). Then on the sidebar to the left click the “gaming” button (is only left side for me…) Then you need to make a new rule and fill in the blanks with this information:

Name: 1
IP address: 2
TCP Ports to open: 43594
UDP Ports to open:
Inbound Filter: Allow All
Schedule: Always[br][size=1]Posted on: January 07, 2007, 03:21:42 AM[/size][hr][quote=“asd”]where i do that in my CPU???

Now we will need to make the rule for your router, by doing this you need to go into your router. Now log into the router and go into “advanced” (at top of screen on mine). Then on the sidebar to the left click the “gaming” button (is only left side for me…) Then you need to make a new rule and fill in the blanks with this information:
